2: PBB<br>Hands: Iksar Scaled<br>Arms: Uthork Hide<br>Shoulders: Lizardscale Mantle<br>Back: Seb Cape<br>Waist: Seb Belt<br>Chest: Mithril BP<br>Legs: Black Chitin Legs <br>Feet: Shimmering Terror Hide<br><br>Weapon: Stave of Shielding<br>Shield: CGS<br><br>I don't want to go crazy, but was seeing if I should have some specific pally armor or something that is relatively cheap to get that is better than what I have. I guess I would spend around 2K in upgrades for this character.<br><br>Thanks a lot!<br><br><br> <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utoffo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toffo1</A> at: 3/11/02 8:32:57 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugilfalas.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gilfalas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 1397<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 8:40:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Paladin</span><hr size=1> What level are you? If your still level one, go back and remake your Paladins with 15 points in Stamina and 5 in wisdom.<br><br>20 in str is frankly a waste.<br><br>As for your gear it is more than fine to see you into the mid to hihg twenties. Just remember that up to about level 50 AC is your absolute best friend as a paladin.<br><br>Stats for melee are pretty much meaningless exept in HUGE quantities. Until level 50+ Max AC and HP gear will do you FAR better that any stat gear can.<br><br>If you upgrade, keep that in mind.<br><br>Post your level and how much your looking to spend. It will help folks suggest what you can use. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105286">Gilfalas Elaandrin</a>, Lvl 59 Knight of Tunare & Defender of Nature<br>Bertoxxulous Server<br><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath">Paladins Of Norrath</a> Messageboard Admin<br>Member of <a href="http://www.fedupnow.com/">Dragon Council</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utoffo1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toffo1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 8:47:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Paladin</span><hr size=1> Thanks for your reply.<br><br>I did post what level (sorta - I said &quot;just started&quot; - level 5 i think)<br><br>I did also say I was willing to spend up to 2K or so :)<br><br>You say restart and put points into STA?<br><br>5 is easy to get again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 139<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/11/02 4:15:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=182.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Newbie Paladin</span><hr size=1> As a Half Elf Paladin, I still regret not putting more points into Sta &amp; Wis when I started... but Keyne was my first character after all.<br><br>Since none of what you have is No Drop (and you're Level 5 or below) I would also recomend restarting.  Put 15 points in Sta and 5 in Wis as was suggested below.  If you can get ahold of a piece of Crusty Armour (or know you can soon) then you might want to just put 10 points into Sta and 10 into Wis.<br><br>For items:<br>Head: Ro Helm or DW Helm is better for you... even though you won't be able to use the DW Helm effect until 45, the AC is nice.  DW Helm runs for 500-800pp<br>Wrists: Hero Bracers (camp with your main if you're 35+ caster, 40+ Melee), Ry'Gorr Bracers, Bracer of Scavenging.<br>Hands: Iksar Scaled are just okay... Gaunts of the Black (about 500-800pp) are prime until you get Planar/Velious.<br>Arms: Give the Ulthork to the Druid and get something with steel.<br>Shoulders: BS Mantle is okay, Crested Spaulders or Tattered Mantle is much better.<br><br>Make sure you get a 1h-slash, 2h-slash &amp; Piercing weapon...  Centi Warspear, Centi SS/LS &amp; BABS are good weapons for this and will carry you for a long, long time.<br><br>Edit: Turn that RMB and PBB over to the Druid as well. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/tdlutenatenjou/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0> at: 3/11/02 4:23:47 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showPrevMessage?topicID=182.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathfrm12.showNextMessage?topicID=182.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pu